23/01/2007
LUXEMBOURG -- Bulgaria's Meglena Kuneva and Romania's Leonard Orban were sworn in as members of the European Commission (EC) during a formal ceremony Monday (January 22nd) at the European Court of Justice. This finalised the procedure for appointing the two new EC members, whose countries joined the EU on January 1st. Kuneva holds the consumer protection portfolio, while Orban is in charge of multilingualism. (Nine o'clock - 23/01/07; BNR, TVR - 22/01/07)
